1
00:00:00,730 --> 00:00:02,719
(Previously)
Kusuma will launch new products.

2
00:00:02,919 --> 00:00:04,968
Which will be the one
and only scent in the world.

3
00:00:04,969 --> 00:00:07,988
What do you mean by a new scent
that will change our company completely?

4
00:00:07,989 --> 00:00:09,969
We used to have one person from Mudan.

5
00:00:09,970 --> 00:00:13,528
And we extracted his body scent
to produce "Bussaba" perfume.

6
00:00:13,529 --> 00:00:15,209
And where are the Mudan people now, Uncle?

7
00:00:20,798 --> 00:00:23,548
- What are you doing here?
- I'm looking for the Mudan tribe.

8
00:00:23,769 --> 00:00:25,688
The tribe with the fragrant scent.
You know them, don't you?

9
00:00:25,689 --> 00:00:26,686
Mata, have you seen Gaysorn?

10
00:00:26,710 --> 00:00:28,439
He mentioned wanting
to go down to the city.

11
00:00:28,440 --> 00:00:31,030
Go find him now!
He must not go down there at any cost.

12
00:00:33,540 --> 00:00:35,139
I think I smell it from…

13
00:00:35,163 --> 00:00:36,256
The scent is gone.

14
00:00:36,380 --> 00:00:37,580
Who are you?

15
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:44,001
Bussaba.

16
00:00:47,480 --> 00:00:48,481
- Bussaba.
- Shhh.

17
00:00:49,297 --> 00:00:52,002
Keep it down, Mata.
Gaysorn just fell asleep.

18
00:01:01,990 --> 00:01:03,120
I went to the market

19
00:01:04,123 --> 00:01:06,500
and someone wanted to give you this.

20
00:01:06,917 --> 00:01:09,100
They said it was a life-or-death situation.

21
00:01:14,683 --> 00:01:15,860
Dear Bussaba,

22
00:01:16,597 --> 00:01:19,380
I was in a car accident and
I want to see you so badly.

23
00:01:19,740 --> 00:01:22,060
Please come to Bangkok as fast as possible.

24
00:01:22,820 --> 00:01:24,540
A person who delivered this letter

25
00:01:24,743 --> 00:01:26,500
will take you here to see me.

26
00:01:27,300 --> 00:01:29,460
Love and miss you so much, Pruek.

27
00:01:39,197 --> 00:01:40,198
What is it?

28
00:01:41,123 --> 00:01:42,180
Hey! Wait!

29
00:01:44,810 --> 00:01:47,780
Wait! Where are you going?
What is going on?

30
00:01:47,890 --> 00:01:49,580
- I need to go.
- Wait.

31
00:01:49,940 --> 00:01:51,060
What is going on?

32
00:01:51,470 --> 00:01:54,060
Pruek was in a car crash
and he's in bad shape.

33
00:01:54,637 --> 00:01:56,220
He wanted to see us.

34
00:01:58,803 --> 00:02:01,910
You can't go! You can't go anywhere.

35
00:02:02,063 --> 00:02:04,940
Don't you remember
how mean these people were?

36
00:02:04,965 --> 00:02:08,622
Who hurt you and caused you
to bring your son back to the mountain?

37
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:12,780
But Pruek has never been mean to me.

38
00:02:13,583 --> 00:02:14,900
Are you going to be so cruel

39
00:02:15,443 --> 00:02:17,310
that you'd stop him from seeing us?

40
00:02:20,223 --> 00:02:21,460
Let's go find your dad.

41
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:24,170
No! You can't go anywhere. I won't let you.

42
00:02:25,110 --> 00:02:26,360
I won't let you go.

43
00:03:40,300 --> 00:03:43,800
"Flower Boy"
(Episode 2)

44
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:50,201
Mata.

45
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:53,027
He fell off the mountain.
I found him so I saved him.

46
00:03:54,220 --> 00:03:55,221
It's true.

47
00:03:55,667 --> 00:03:57,627
I'm just a traveler
and I got lost in the forest.

48
00:03:58,277 --> 00:04:00,117
- Liar! Tell me the truth!
- Hey!

49
00:04:01,037 --> 00:04:02,038
Can you put it away?

50
00:04:02,567 --> 00:04:04,647
I just got lost in the forest,
you don't have to harm me.

51
00:04:04,794 --> 00:04:05,877
Isn't it illegal?

52
00:04:05,993 --> 00:04:07,963
- Nobody knows about the law in the forest.
- Tawan!

53
00:04:08,147 --> 00:04:10,077
Tawan, calm down. Don't threaten him.

54
00:04:10,980 --> 00:04:13,707
He just got lost in the woods,
don't make a big deal out of it.

55
00:04:14,314 --> 00:04:16,197
I'll send him off
at the edge tomorrow morning.

56
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:21,907
Tawan, you need to watch him tonight.

57
00:04:22,407 --> 00:04:25,317
Tawan, you can drop him off

58
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:28,077
when you go to the market tomorrow.

59
00:04:28,807 --> 00:04:30,237
- Mata, but…
- Stop.

60
00:04:30,997 --> 00:04:32,797
Or you want him to be sent off tonight?

61
00:04:34,534 --> 00:04:36,067
Go! You need to come with me.

62
00:04:40,214 --> 00:04:41,215
Hey!

63
00:04:56,887 --> 00:04:58,567
My mom's house is far from others' houses.

64
00:04:58,767 --> 00:05:01,357
He got lost and he was injured.

65
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:03,527
I checked and he was unarmed.

66
00:05:03,734 --> 00:05:05,357
He shouldn't be a danger to us.

67
00:05:05,527 --> 00:05:08,117
You can't trust an outsider
with an innocent face.

68
00:05:08,207 --> 00:05:10,517
- Take your mom for example.
- We didn't know about that.

69
00:05:10,734 --> 00:05:13,717
Mata, I didn't even know
what happened to Mom.

70
00:05:14,454 --> 00:05:15,934
Who witnessed it with their own eyes?

71
00:05:16,607 --> 00:05:18,234
Maybe she is still alive.

72
00:05:19,094 --> 00:05:21,597
Maybe there is something stopping her
from coming back to me.

73
00:05:22,834 --> 00:05:25,114
Maybe she is waiting
for me to look for her.

74
00:05:26,474 --> 00:05:27,714
You're helping him,

75
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:30,620
hoping that you could
go to the city with him, aren't you?

76
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:34,940
I helped him because he was injured.

77
00:05:36,987 --> 00:05:37,988
But…

78
00:05:38,567 --> 00:05:41,000
- if he could take me…
- Stop thinking about that.

79
00:05:42,520 --> 00:05:44,020
You have to stay here.

80
00:05:44,567 --> 00:05:47,514
Your mom disappeared
because I couldn't stop her in time.

81
00:05:48,674 --> 00:05:51,614
And I won't let that happen again.

82
00:05:53,367 --> 00:05:54,368
Get inside.

83
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:57,340
- Mata.
- Get inside and never leave this place.

84
00:05:58,960 --> 00:05:59,961
Go!

85
00:07:24,867 --> 00:07:25,868
Hey!

86
00:07:29,474 --> 00:07:30,475
What are you doing?

87
00:07:35,154 --> 00:07:36,155
It's cold.

88
00:07:37,787 --> 00:07:39,587
So I was going to shut the window.

89
00:07:47,027 --> 00:07:48,028
That's it.

90
00:07:49,160 --> 00:07:50,161
Hey!

91
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:52,121
Calm down.

92
00:07:58,060 --> 00:07:59,357
I'm about to go to bed.

93
00:08:07,674 --> 00:08:08,675
I'm tired.

94
00:08:09,547 --> 00:08:10,548
Good night.

95
00:08:24,077 --> 00:08:26,336
If you're planning to visit the place,
find someone to go with.

96
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:28,200
Don't go there by yourself,
it's too dangerous.

97
00:08:29,607 --> 00:08:30,608
Is it dangerous?

98
00:08:31,114 --> 00:08:33,774
Mudan people don't like strangers.

99
00:08:34,127 --> 00:08:35,480
They could hurt you.

100
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:38,157
You need to be vigilant about this.

101
00:08:52,277 --> 00:08:53,974
Wake up! Up!

102
00:08:58,027 --> 00:08:59,028
Hurry up!

103
00:08:59,060 --> 00:09:00,774
I know! I'm up now.

104
00:09:06,497 --> 00:09:07,498
Get changed.

105
00:09:07,627 --> 00:09:08,628
Go!

106
00:09:12,860 --> 00:09:14,357
Where is Gaysorn?

107
00:09:14,917 --> 00:09:15,918
Why?

108
00:09:17,287 --> 00:09:18,887
You don't want me to say goodbye to him?

109
00:09:19,077 --> 00:09:20,637
No need to. Hurry up!

110
00:09:32,174 --> 00:09:33,957
- Come on!
- Fine, I know!

111
00:09:34,054 --> 00:09:36,014
I need to attend a wedding
after dropping you off.

112
00:09:39,247 --> 00:09:40,477
There is a wedding?

113
00:09:40,507 --> 00:09:43,674
That's right. Everyone in the
tribe needs to be witnesses.

114
00:09:44,587 --> 00:09:45,588
Ouch!

115
00:09:45,937 --> 00:09:46,957
I know! Okay!

116
00:09:49,394 --> 00:09:50,420
Can I wash my face first?

117
00:09:51,067 --> 00:09:52,514
Go ahead!

118
00:10:13,367 --> 00:10:14,368
Ouch!

119
00:10:15,574 --> 00:10:17,597
Hey! What's wrong?

120
00:10:18,437 --> 00:10:19,874
- You!
- Ow!

121
00:10:20,087 --> 00:10:21,088
Hey!

122
00:10:23,147 --> 00:10:24,637
Hey!

123
00:10:25,357 --> 00:10:27,317
Hey! Wake up!

124
00:10:27,997 --> 00:10:28,998
Hey!

125
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:36,494
Tawan.

126
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:38,121
What did you do to him?

127
00:10:38,494 --> 00:10:40,734
Nothing. Suddenly, he yelled

128
00:10:41,214 --> 00:10:42,717
and went like this 'Ouch!'.

129
00:10:43,037 --> 00:10:44,514
Ouch!

130
00:10:45,717 --> 00:10:46,797
Then he fell to the ground.

131
00:10:49,314 --> 00:10:50,315
Are you sure?

132
00:10:50,874 --> 00:10:52,277
I've never lied to you, Gaysorn.

133
00:10:54,554 --> 00:10:55,597
So what happened to him?

134
00:10:56,774 --> 00:10:58,054
He looked much better yesterday.

135
00:10:58,634 --> 00:11:00,197
Hey!

136
00:11:01,107 --> 00:11:02,108
How are you feeling?

137
00:11:02,208 --> 00:11:03,209
Gaysorn,

138
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:06,601
suddenly my head hurt

139
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:10,240
and I saw the ground spinning.

140
00:11:12,254 --> 00:11:14,255
Ouch!

141
00:11:14,637 --> 00:11:17,374
You should rest,
you can't fall again or it will get worse.

142
00:11:21,460 --> 00:11:22,517
What are we going to do?

143
00:11:24,480 --> 00:11:26,277
What do you mean? He can't even get up.

144
00:11:28,837 --> 00:11:30,797
We can tie him up
and carry him down the mountain.

145
00:11:32,194 --> 00:11:34,074
What if he dies along the way?

146
00:11:34,780 --> 00:11:37,000
Tawan, he can't make it.

147
00:11:37,927 --> 00:11:39,517
We can let him stay for one more night.

148
00:11:40,407 --> 00:11:42,247
- But Mata said…
- I'll talk to Mata about him.

149
00:11:49,640 --> 00:11:50,640
Fine.

150
00:11:50,641 --> 00:11:51,717
Are you sure about that?

151
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:55,877
We can't let our people

152
00:11:56,047 --> 00:11:57,647
carry him all the way down the mountain.

153
00:11:57,960 --> 00:11:59,960
We won't make it in time
for the wedding reception.

154
00:12:03,687 --> 00:12:04,974
Let's do that,

155
00:12:05,894 --> 00:12:06,895
okay?

156
00:12:08,594 --> 00:12:10,117
Come on, Mata. Don't you worry.

157
00:12:10,567 --> 00:12:13,360
That outsider can't even get up and walk.

158
00:12:13,874 --> 00:12:15,400
He won't cause us any troubles.

159
00:12:19,910 --> 00:12:21,150
I got one person to believe me.

160
00:13:05,783 --> 00:13:06,784
Flowers?

161
00:13:07,996 --> 00:13:10,197
Mudan people have deep
connections with flowers.

162
00:13:10,907 --> 00:13:12,660
Your dad told me that

163
00:13:13,687 --> 00:13:15,917
they basically communicated
through flowers.

164
00:13:16,917 --> 00:13:18,917
Just keep your eyes
peeled for this sort of thing.

165
00:13:34,380 --> 00:13:36,437
Come on, let's eat.

166
00:13:39,420 --> 00:13:40,421
Okay.

167
00:13:45,597 --> 00:13:46,598
Let's go. Let's eat.

168
00:13:56,134 --> 00:13:57,917
I got some bananas here.

169
00:14:00,407 --> 00:14:01,408
Mata,

170
00:14:03,027 --> 00:14:04,954
can I get some rice and eggs?

171
00:14:08,594 --> 00:14:09,677
I'll give it to him.

172
00:14:10,547 --> 00:14:11,717
He should be up by now.

173
00:14:13,397 --> 00:14:15,320
He can have only what we provide.

174
00:14:24,154 --> 00:14:24,755
Here, take it.

175
00:14:24,797 --> 00:14:25,798
Thank you.

176
00:14:31,074 --> 00:14:32,957
It's getting hot. I'll give it to him.

177
00:14:45,477 --> 00:14:47,517
Come back here and eat.

178
00:14:50,374 --> 00:14:51,375
Gaysorn!

179
00:14:54,257 --> 00:14:55,258
Gaysorn!

180
00:14:56,797 --> 00:14:58,197
Gaysorn!

181
00:14:58,597 --> 00:14:59,597
Gaysorn!

182
00:15:00,094 --> 00:15:01,095
Gaysorn!

183
00:15:01,317 --> 00:15:02,597
Hey!

184
00:15:06,900 --> 00:15:07,901
Hey!

185
00:15:08,077 --> 00:15:09,597
I've been looking for you for so long.

186
00:15:09,740 --> 00:15:10,741
I…

187
00:15:12,620 --> 00:15:13,974
Hey! You!

188
00:15:15,627 --> 00:15:16,628
Hey!

189
00:15:20,187 --> 00:15:21,797
Hey! Hey!

190
00:15:22,957 --> 00:15:23,958
You!

191
00:15:25,447 --> 00:15:26,448
Gaysorn.

192
00:15:27,160 --> 00:15:29,287
I've been looking for you, Gaysorn.

193
00:15:33,594 --> 00:15:34,595
How are you feeling?

194
00:15:36,834 --> 00:15:38,447
- What is it?
- I want to know.

195
00:15:40,340 --> 00:15:41,341
Why are you here?

196
00:15:42,100 --> 00:15:44,247
I woke up and I didn't see anybody.

197
00:15:45,114 --> 00:15:46,880
So I walked around to searched for you.

198
00:15:47,900 --> 00:15:50,060
What is the celebration for?

199
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:51,947
It seems like so much fun.

200
00:15:56,640 --> 00:15:58,137
Right, I knew it.

201
00:15:59,160 --> 00:16:00,277
Is it the wedding?

202
00:16:01,480 --> 00:16:02,757
Tawan told me this morning.

203
00:16:04,160 --> 00:16:05,894
A wedding of the people here.

204
00:16:07,667 --> 00:16:08,668
I…

205
00:16:10,380 --> 00:16:11,820
Can I stay and watch?

206
00:16:12,580 --> 00:16:14,700
I don't want to go back to
the cottage all by myself.

207
00:16:15,197 --> 00:16:16,198
I'm scared

208
00:16:17,087 --> 00:16:18,088
and I need some water.

209
00:16:19,360 --> 00:16:20,361
Tawan.

210
00:16:23,240 --> 00:16:24,537
Can I have some water please?

211
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:27,561
Go.

212
00:16:27,874 --> 00:16:29,637
- Oh, come on!
- Just go.

213
00:16:29,654 --> 00:16:30,837
You're hurting me!

214
00:16:44,934 --> 00:16:45,935
You're such a big mouth.

215
00:16:46,860 --> 00:16:48,243
I just told him that there was
going to be a wedding

216
00:16:48,267 --> 00:16:49,437
and that was it.

217
00:16:51,374 --> 00:16:53,974
It is getting out of hand
and we can't hide anymore.

218
00:17:03,914 --> 00:17:05,794
If you don't feel comfortable
having me around,

219
00:17:06,267 --> 00:17:07,517
then I can go back.

220
00:17:13,020 --> 00:17:14,267
You're Mudan people.

221
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:18,637
And what would I do with that information?

222
00:17:19,700 --> 00:17:22,337
- Hey! Calm down!
- Tawan!

223
00:17:23,880 --> 00:17:25,507
- Wait!
- Tawan.

224
00:17:28,887 --> 00:17:31,277
You don't have to kill me over this?

225
00:17:32,547 --> 00:17:34,237
Who is meaner?

226
00:17:35,074 --> 00:17:37,517
The mountain people or city people?

227
00:17:46,474 --> 00:17:47,475
We…

228
00:17:48,757 --> 00:17:50,820
the people from your place used to hurt us.

229
00:17:53,227 --> 00:17:54,797
We needed to relocate.

230
00:17:57,767 --> 00:18:00,007
That's why we cut off
all the contact with outsiders.

231
00:18:00,594 --> 00:18:02,597
Because we don't want them

232
00:18:03,560 --> 00:18:04,877
to hurt us anymore.

233
00:18:06,460 --> 00:18:07,477
Especially Gaysorn.

234
00:18:12,314 --> 00:18:13,315
Oh my!

235
00:18:14,940 --> 00:18:16,877
I would never hurt him.

236
00:18:17,880 --> 00:18:21,000
He saved my life, why would I hurt him?

237
00:18:22,167 --> 00:18:25,077
If you don't want anyone to find out
that you're here,

238
00:18:25,689 --> 00:18:27,740
then I won't tell anyone. I promise.

239
00:18:30,554 --> 00:18:31,797
I just want to be your friend.

240
00:18:34,074 --> 00:18:35,437
To be Gaysorn's friend.

241
00:18:38,197 --> 00:18:39,597
We can't trust the outsiders.

242
00:18:48,767 --> 00:18:49,768
But I trust him.

243
00:18:53,317 --> 00:18:54,318
Mata.

244
00:18:55,347 --> 00:18:56,597
Those who hurt mom

245
00:18:57,107 --> 00:18:58,637
have nothing to do with him.

246
00:19:00,900 --> 00:19:03,594
Don't blame him for
others' horrible behavior.

247
00:19:07,880 --> 00:19:09,360
I believe that Scent is a good person

248
00:19:11,727 --> 00:19:12,877
and he won't hurt me.

249
00:19:14,757 --> 00:19:15,758
Thank you.

250
00:19:34,854 --> 00:19:37,877
I sent someone to look at the spot
where the huntsman split with Mr. Scent.

251
00:19:38,717 --> 00:19:40,917
But it rained heavily last night

252
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:43,600
and it destroyed all the
footprints on the ground.

253
00:19:44,814 --> 00:19:46,677
Is it possible that

254
00:19:46,754 --> 00:19:48,754
Scent walked further into
the forest, around here?

255
00:19:49,654 --> 00:19:51,307
We expanded our searching area

256
00:19:51,980 --> 00:19:53,500
but the woods here are so complicated.

257
00:19:54,100 --> 00:19:57,214
If we pass this area, it will be too deep.

258
00:19:57,960 --> 00:20:00,314
The trail will be steep,
and it's too dangerous.

259
00:20:01,694 --> 00:20:03,440
Can I join the team?

260
00:20:03,554 --> 00:20:05,157
I can't just stay still and do nothing.

261
00:20:06,294 --> 00:20:07,534
I don't think it's a good idea.

262
00:20:08,237 --> 00:20:10,937
People with no experience
are not suggested to go.

263
00:20:11,414 --> 00:20:14,274
If there is a mistake,
we will need to look for you as well.

264
00:20:52,467 --> 00:20:54,627
Mudan people don't fall in love

265
00:20:55,700 --> 00:20:57,117
with appearances.

266
00:20:57,927 --> 00:21:02,047
Instead, they fall in love
with the scent which is bonding

267
00:21:02,574 --> 00:21:04,187
the two of you together.

268
00:21:12,757 --> 00:21:14,277
From now on,

269
00:21:15,494 --> 00:21:19,117
your hearts will become one.

270
00:21:40,734 --> 00:21:42,567
The ancestors have acknowledged

271
00:21:42,957 --> 00:21:45,434
your good intentions already.

272
00:21:45,874 --> 00:21:47,557
The ritual has ended.

273
00:21:49,037 --> 00:21:50,997
- Congratulations.
- Yeah, congrats.

274
00:22:19,507 --> 00:22:21,197
Mudan's wedding ceremony is quite simple

275
00:22:22,757 --> 00:22:23,758
yet it is so cute.

276
00:22:26,380 --> 00:22:28,180
Why don't you want
the outsiders to see this?

277
00:22:37,037 --> 00:22:38,538
Wildflowers are so beautiful.

278
00:22:39,517 --> 00:22:40,518
Their beauty

279
00:22:42,047 --> 00:22:43,537
doesn't need anyone's validation.

280
00:22:46,694 --> 00:22:47,695
That's so deep.

281
00:22:50,687 --> 00:22:53,614
Besides the flowers from up here,

282
00:22:54,747 --> 00:22:56,627
do you want to see flowers
from somewhere else?

283
00:22:57,994 --> 00:22:59,074
They are equally beautiful.

284
00:23:27,266 --> 00:23:30,303
This is Bangkok at night.

285
00:23:31,107 --> 00:23:33,437
Wow! So pretty.

286
00:23:33,980 --> 00:23:34,980
Here, hold it.

287
00:23:43,614 --> 00:23:44,637
You can do it like this.

288
00:23:49,277 --> 00:23:51,077
- What?
- See? Now you can watch it clearer.

289
00:23:56,547 --> 00:23:57,548
And this one

290
00:23:58,574 --> 00:24:00,957
is the sea.

291
00:24:01,627 --> 00:24:02,660
It is not in Bangkok

292
00:24:03,407 --> 00:24:04,934
but we can drive there for two hours.

293
00:24:09,837 --> 00:24:11,637
The sea is blue like this?

294
00:24:13,807 --> 00:24:14,808
So pretty.

295
00:24:17,117 --> 00:24:18,118
That's right, pretty.

296
00:24:27,727 --> 00:24:28,728
What?

297
00:24:29,997 --> 00:24:30,998
It's gone.

298
00:24:32,460 --> 00:24:33,461
It runs out of battery.

299
00:24:34,680 --> 00:24:37,157
They need electricity to function.

300
00:24:38,427 --> 00:24:41,647
Like people, we need to eat to fuel up.

301
00:24:44,717 --> 00:24:46,700
If you want to see
beautiful places like these,

302
00:24:47,174 --> 00:24:48,175
there is only way out.

303
00:24:50,367 --> 00:24:51,967
You need to see them with your own eyes.

304
00:24:56,294 --> 00:24:57,774
Do you want to visit Bangkok with me?

305
00:24:59,354 --> 00:25:01,740
I will take you places
you've never been to.

306
00:25:02,760 --> 00:25:04,237
If you want to search for your mom,

307
00:25:04,900 --> 00:25:05,901
I can help you with that.

308
00:25:09,260 --> 00:25:10,261
Can you?

309
00:25:10,877 --> 00:25:11,878
Sure, I can.

310
00:25:43,920 --> 00:25:45,437
But we need to leave tonight,

311
00:25:45,834 --> 00:25:47,794
when everyone is attending
the wedding reception.

312
00:26:06,674 --> 00:26:08,240
I will search for Mom in Bangkok.

313
00:26:08,980 --> 00:26:11,467
I will be gone for a month
and I will be right back.

314
00:26:12,357 --> 00:26:13,358
Don't worry about me.

315
00:26:35,094 --> 00:26:36,687
Hey! Gaysorn!

316
00:26:37,300 --> 00:26:38,757
This way!

317
00:26:43,500 --> 00:26:45,500
You took so long,
I thought you changed your mind.

318
00:26:51,594 --> 00:26:52,595
Should we go?

319
00:26:54,207 --> 00:26:55,208
Let's go.

320
00:26:58,340 --> 00:27:00,517
Stop, right now! Where are you going?

321
00:27:00,667 --> 00:27:01,668
Gaysorn! Run!

322
00:27:03,280 --> 00:27:04,281
Hurry up!

323
00:27:07,720 --> 00:27:08,721
Gaysorn!

324
00:27:10,874 --> 00:27:11,875
Hey!

325
00:27:14,080 --> 00:27:16,757
- Stop it, Gaysorn. Why are you doing this?
- Let me go.

326
00:27:18,437 --> 00:27:19,734
Keep them in the granary.

327
00:27:29,667 --> 00:27:30,668
Stay still.

328
00:27:31,080 --> 00:27:32,987
You're hurting me. Let me go!

329
00:27:34,034 --> 00:27:36,194
- I told you to let me go!
- You can't untie it easily.

330
00:27:36,357 --> 00:27:37,358
Let me go.

331
00:27:37,960 --> 00:27:38,961
Stop talking.

332
00:27:45,500 --> 00:27:47,580
Mata told me to keep both of you in here.

333
00:27:48,149 --> 00:27:49,589
I will release you tomorrow morning.

334
00:27:50,077 --> 00:27:52,680
And I will be the one to drop him off.

335
00:27:53,567 --> 00:27:54,568
Why?

336
00:27:57,317 --> 00:27:59,740
Hey! Come back here!

337
00:28:01,460 --> 00:28:02,461
Tawan!

338
00:28:03,087 --> 00:28:04,087
Tawan!

339
00:28:13,074 --> 00:28:15,557
You should get back to the reception,
I will watch them here.

340
00:28:36,154 --> 00:28:37,155
Hey!

341
00:28:40,574 --> 00:28:43,254
I'm sorry for putting you in this position.

342
00:28:45,074 --> 00:28:46,797
It's my fault too.

343
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:49,687
I want to search for Mom.

344
00:28:50,587 --> 00:28:51,797
This is out of line.

345
00:28:53,837 --> 00:28:54,838
I will not stand for it.

346
00:28:55,554 --> 00:28:57,674
I will take you to
search for your mom no matter what.

347
00:29:05,607 --> 00:29:07,357
Hey! Can you twist to the opposite side?

348
00:29:08,317 --> 00:29:10,137
One… two… three!

349
00:29:14,060 --> 00:29:15,061
Come on, harder!

350
00:29:20,520 --> 00:29:21,757
Ouch! Hey!

351
00:29:22,747 --> 00:29:24,827
I think it's getting tighter when we pull.

352
00:29:47,587 --> 00:29:50,427
I think we need to scoot to that pole.

353
00:29:51,157 --> 00:29:52,158
That pole.

354
00:29:53,197 --> 00:29:54,198
Let's go.

355
00:29:56,157 --> 00:29:57,158
Hang in there.

356
00:30:01,740 --> 00:30:03,357
Almost there, let's go.

357
00:30:07,274 --> 00:30:08,275
We are almost there.

358
00:30:11,667 --> 00:30:12,668
A little bit more.

359
00:30:27,694 --> 00:30:28,695
Harder, okay?

360
00:30:47,694 --> 00:30:48,695
We're close.

361
00:30:59,947 --> 00:31:00,948
Hey!

362
00:31:05,479 --> 00:31:06,480
What the heck?

363
00:31:07,954 --> 00:31:08,955
Hey!

364
00:31:12,437 --> 00:31:13,438
Hey!

365
00:31:18,781 --> 00:31:20,077
- Tawan!
- Gaysorn!

366
00:31:20,440 --> 00:31:21,441
- Tawan!
- Let's go.

367
00:31:22,517 --> 00:31:23,877
- Hurry up!
- Gaysorn!

368
00:31:24,620 --> 00:31:25,621
Gaysorn!

369
00:31:31,797 --> 00:31:33,717
Fire! Fire!

370
00:31:37,214 --> 00:31:38,215
Hey!

371
00:31:46,580 --> 00:31:47,581
Which way to go?

372
00:31:49,581 --> 00:31:50,582
No idea.

373
00:31:52,147 --> 00:31:53,467
Let's try on this side, let's go.

374
00:31:56,826 --> 00:32:00,116
Fire! Hurry up, I need your help!

375
00:32:03,920 --> 00:32:06,521
Fire! Come on!

376
00:32:15,894 --> 00:32:17,437
Hurry up! Come on.

377
00:32:17,487 --> 00:32:19,917
Stop the fire! Hey!

378
00:32:21,049 --> 00:32:23,197
- What is going on?
- Gaysorn ran away with him.

379
00:32:23,347 --> 00:32:24,877
- What?
- He took Gaysorn with him!

380
00:32:26,320 --> 00:32:29,397
- They're gone!
- I heard that!

381
00:32:29,734 --> 00:32:31,357
But we need to stop the fire first,

382
00:32:31,437 --> 00:32:33,077
we can talk about that later. Let's go!

383
00:32:36,679 --> 00:32:37,680
Hurry up.

384
00:33:00,420 --> 00:33:02,197
We can't go any further than this.

385
00:33:04,237 --> 00:33:05,238
This spot.

386
00:33:07,094 --> 00:33:09,197
Let's go. We should look over there.

387
00:33:11,214 --> 00:33:12,215
Let's go.

388
00:33:13,437 --> 00:33:15,557
Gaysorn! Wake up!

389
00:33:15,834 --> 00:33:16,835
Come on! Wake up!

390
00:33:17,317 --> 00:33:20,237
Hey! Hey!

391
00:33:28,607 --> 00:33:29,608
Are you Scent?

392
00:33:34,197 --> 00:33:35,357
Where have you been hiding?

393
00:34:10,827 --> 00:34:12,677
Thank you so much everyone.

394
00:34:14,180 --> 00:34:15,700
You're feeling better now, aren't you?

395
00:34:15,917 --> 00:34:16,918
Thank you.

396
00:34:17,157 --> 00:34:18,158
Thank you.

397
00:34:23,667 --> 00:34:24,668
How are you feeling?

398
00:34:25,747 --> 00:34:28,117
What do you think? Took you long enough.

399
00:34:28,314 --> 00:34:29,557
I came here as fast as I can.

400
00:34:33,387 --> 00:34:34,388
Who is he?

401
00:34:38,640 --> 00:34:39,641
Mudan.

402
00:34:40,500 --> 00:34:41,501
Mudan?

403
00:34:59,914 --> 00:35:00,915
It's coffee.

404
00:35:02,140 --> 00:35:03,141
I know.

405
00:35:03,810 --> 00:35:05,603
They are planting so many
coffee beans in the mountain.

406
00:35:05,694 --> 00:35:06,760
I know what it is.

407
00:35:08,414 --> 00:35:10,934
It's not like that. I didn't mean
that you didn't know about it.

408
00:35:11,947 --> 00:35:13,187
I just wanted you to have some.

409
00:35:15,900 --> 00:35:16,901
Gaysorn,

410
00:35:17,387 --> 00:35:18,557
this is Sun. He is my friend.

411
00:35:20,080 --> 00:35:21,957
Sun, this is Gaysorn.

412
00:35:23,787 --> 00:35:24,788
Hello.

413
00:35:25,354 --> 00:35:26,355
Hello.

414
00:35:27,289 --> 00:35:29,957
I fell off the mountain
and Gaysorn saved me.

415
00:35:31,340 --> 00:35:33,300
He has to run some errands in Bangkok.

416
00:35:34,627 --> 00:35:35,947
So I invited him to come with me.

417
00:35:39,180 --> 00:35:41,820
Okay, we should head back this afternoon.

418
00:35:42,894 --> 00:35:43,895
I'll book you a flight.

419
00:35:50,454 --> 00:35:51,455
Mr. Gaysorn,

420
00:35:51,854 --> 00:35:54,797
I'm going to need your ID card.

421
00:35:56,187 --> 00:35:57,188
I don't have one.

422
00:36:01,520 --> 00:36:02,521
What are you going to do?

423
00:36:03,620 --> 00:36:04,621
I will handle it.

424
00:36:28,680 --> 00:36:29,681
How was it?

425
00:36:30,814 --> 00:36:33,917
My eyes and my nose hurt, how was it?

426
00:36:37,837 --> 00:36:39,407
The granary was so old.

427
00:36:40,827 --> 00:36:42,127
The fire spread so fast.

428
00:36:44,437 --> 00:36:45,677
It was nothing compare to this.

429
00:36:46,587 --> 00:36:49,254
It started to crack and fire fell on

430
00:36:49,940 --> 00:36:51,837
our people's houses around the area.

431
00:36:53,434 --> 00:36:54,874
They are facing so much damage.

432
00:37:25,327 --> 00:37:26,328
Hey!

433
00:37:28,860 --> 00:37:29,861
Hey!

434
00:37:32,334 --> 00:37:34,014
Are you going to do
that the whole way home?

435
00:37:36,514 --> 00:37:38,074
Everything is so new and strange to me.

436
00:37:39,442 --> 00:37:41,040
I've never expected to see any of this.

437
00:39:25,400 --> 00:39:26,917
- Let's go.
- Wow!

438
00:39:27,980 --> 00:39:28,981
Is this your house?

439
00:39:31,674 --> 00:39:33,277
Come in.

440
00:39:58,174 --> 00:39:59,175
Welcome.

441
00:40:00,340 --> 00:40:02,477
This is my place. Make yourself at home.

442
00:40:46,354 --> 00:40:47,355
We're here.

443
00:40:47,837 --> 00:40:48,838
Wow!

444
00:40:49,827 --> 00:40:51,300
It's even better than the picture.

445
00:40:57,980 --> 00:41:00,094
Welcome to Bangkok, Gaysorn.

446
00:41:17,507 --> 00:41:19,077
Scent got a person from Mudan already.

447
00:41:22,287 --> 00:41:24,197
My nephew is quite good at this.

448
00:41:26,477 --> 00:41:27,478
Follow me.

449
00:41:29,207 --> 00:41:30,537
This is your bathroom.

450
00:41:37,394 --> 00:41:38,677
This way

451
00:41:39,694 --> 00:41:40,717
is shower area.

452
00:41:44,700 --> 00:41:46,957
This one is for washing your hair,

453
00:41:47,717 --> 00:41:49,077
this one is for washing your body.

454
00:41:50,254 --> 00:41:52,717
This is the shower head,
you can use this one

455
00:41:53,397 --> 00:41:54,797
or the showerhead right here.

456
00:41:57,114 --> 00:42:00,197
You can adjust hot and cold water here.

457
00:42:02,020 --> 00:42:03,021
I can?

458
00:42:09,240 --> 00:42:10,241
- What?
- Hey! Relax.

459
00:42:11,540 --> 00:42:14,397
Calm down, it's just water.

460
00:42:23,980 --> 00:42:24,981
It's too cold.

461
00:42:28,117 --> 00:42:29,557
You can adjust it to be warmer here.

462
00:43:48,400 --> 00:43:49,600
Your face is flushed.

463
00:43:50,190 --> 00:43:51,410
Are you okay?

464
00:43:52,069 --> 00:43:54,270
Is it because the fire is reflecting on it?

465
00:43:56,490 --> 00:43:57,490
Hey.

466
00:43:59,025 --> 00:44:02,066
Take a close look, is my face really red?

467
00:44:03,420 --> 00:44:04,420
Hmm.

468
00:44:04,890 --> 00:44:08,219
Actually, I think your
face is redder than mine.

469
00:44:18,000 --> 00:44:19,769
I smell that fragrance again.

470
00:44:27,530 --> 00:44:28,730
I think...

471
00:44:29,149 --> 00:44:30,359
this scent...

472
00:44:30,979 --> 00:44:33,069
it must be coming from you.

473
00:44:33,869 --> 00:44:34,869
Right?

474
00:44:42,140 --> 00:44:43,140
Hmm.

475
00:44:44,380 --> 00:44:45,580
It smells so good.

476
00:44:57,900 --> 00:44:59,700
(Next Episode)

477
00:44:59,719 --> 00:45:02,579
Actually, you look
quite cute in my clothes.

478
00:45:02,580 --> 00:45:05,290
Now that we have the Mudan,
take the best possible care of him.

479
00:45:08,889 --> 00:45:11,239
Do you really not know
who Scent used to date?

480
00:45:12,109 --> 00:45:14,179
Gaysorn doesn't smell like that
all the time, you know.

481
00:45:14,180 --> 00:45:17,388
A person's body scent
depends on many factors.

482
00:45:17,389 --> 00:45:21,419
I have no idea what actually
triggers the Mudan's fragrance.
